<br>
 <p>Lexxi Ledenyetz<BR>
42nd Prayer<BR>
Cleric of Brell<BR>
Ak'Anon<BR>
Heiress and Officer of the Ledenyetz Troupe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 876<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 11:24:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2252.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC soft cap and such?</span><hr size=1> My knowledge on this is only second hand, but here's what I've heard.<br>
<br>
There's a so called soft cap on AC for each class.  Above this point, there's greatly deminishing returns as to how much each new point of AC actually helps to mitigate damage taken.  For warriors I believe this is between 1200 and 1300, and other classes have lower soft caps.  In fact, all stats have soft caps or hard caps other than HPs (well, it's just rumors on resist caps).  This is why high end warriors care so much about thier hit points above all other things, and why many other classes do as well... for example, I'm maxing HP and AC right now, since in raid buffs I bump into 255 strength and 255 dex, which I can't get above.  <br>
<br>
Agility has a slight soft cap at 200, as do all stats of it's type (Dex, Str, Int, etc).  Each of these provide less benifit above 200, but the difference isn't as extream as the AC soft cap, so it's still worth while to keep on adding to these stats until you find them bumping into 255, which is their hard cap.  Note that the effect of agility on non rangers and monks is very slight... when I swamped out a Ravenscale Breastplate (19 AC, no AGI) for a Haze Panther Tunic (14 AC, 20 AGI) my ac went down by a bit.  However, there's a breakpoint at 75 AGI... dropping below that will seriously hurt your AC.  But above 75 each point doesn't matter all that much.<br>
<br>
Dex's effect on procing isn't all that huge, but it's there.<br>
<br>
A good place to ask about soft caps and such is www.thesafehouse.com, in their message boards, which are argueably the best boards out there for high level information.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
Dawn Rising <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A> at: 7/5/02 11:27:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulacus1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lacus1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 2:29:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2252.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC soft cap and such?</span><hr size=1> Soft caps are relative to MOBs... for something like a moss snake, the soft cap is probably something like 200 AC or less -- a 1400 AC warrior won't tank it much better than a 800 AC enchanter.  But generally, the softcap refers to the maximum cap for &quot;lesser&quot; uber MOBs -- Vindicator, Tormax, Yelinak, etc.  This turns out to be around 1350 for warriors with stability3.  For MOBs like Emperor Ssra, Tunare, AoW, the ATK rating of the MOB is far too high for a reasonable AC to meet it (it's like a 200 AC lvl 15 enchanter tanking a kobold named in Velk's vs. a 400 AC lvl 20 enchanter).  There's not really a middle ground between the AC-able MOBs and the non-AC-able. <p>--Lacus<br>Grandmaster<br>
<a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bawakenedsouls">Awakened Souls</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulacus1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lacus1</A> at: 7/5/02 2:35:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BakoFV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Ladies Leezard</span><br>  Posts: 291<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/02 4:08:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2252.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC soft cap and such?</span><hr size=1> Verant has never relaeased any *proof* about ac. They release BS statements by guys who make the game but dont play it. They say there is no cap, But the people who strive to be the best in the game, play the game, and they can tell the difference, I have seen no writen proof but I have seen proof by experience and the experience of these people. Fire of Heavens, Afterlife and people of this calaber.<br>
<br>
